Canadian-American actor, screenwriter, producer and director Jason Reitman's fourth feature film which was written by American screenwriter and author Diablo Cody, was screened Out of competition at the 62nd Berlin International Film Festival in 2012 and is an American production which was shot on locations in Minneapolis, Minnesota and New York City, New York in USA and produced by Diablo Cody, Jason Reitman, Lianne Halfon, Mason Novick, Russell Smith and Charlize Theron. It tells the story about Mavis Gary-Crane, a 37-year-old female ghost writer for a young adult novel series called the Waverly Prep who lives in an apartment in Minneapolis, Minnesota. After receiving an e-mail from her high school boyfriend Buddy Slade and his wife Beth with pictures of their newborn daughter, Mavis interprets it as a sign that she and Buddy are meant to be together and decides to return to her hometown in Mercury, Minnesota with her dog Dolce.

Finely and acutely directed by Canadian-American filmmaker Jason Reitman, this quietly paced and engaging fictional tale which is narrated mostly from the protagonist's point of view, draws an incisive portrayal of a somewhat conflicted woman's attempt to regain her first true love and her relationship with a bachelor who lives with his sister. While notable for its naturalistic milieu depictions, fine cinematography by cinematographer Eric Steelberg and costume design by costume designer David C. Robinson, this character-driven and dialog-driven comedy-drama depicts a nuanced study of character.

This darkly humorous and somewhat romantic story is impelled and reinforced by its cogent narrative structure, subtle character development and continuity, colorful characters, quick-witted dialog and the poignant acting performances by South-African-American actress Charlize Theron and American stand-up comedian, writer and actor Patton Oswalt. A charming and commendable independent film.
